---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'top-picks', text: 'Our Top Picks', level: 2 },
  { id: 'leaving-pakistan', text: 'Leaving Pakistani Healthcare', level: 2 },
  { id: 'destination-considerations', text: 'Destination Considerations', level: 2 },
  { id: 'comparison-table', text: 'Quick Comparison', level: 2 },
  { id: 'detailed-reviews', text: 'Detailed Reviews', level: 2 },
  { id: 'popular-destinations', text: 'Popular Destinations', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Cigna Global Review', href: '/providers/cigna-global' },
  { title: 'Bupa Global Review', href: '/providers/bupa-global' },
  { title: 'Best UK Expat Insurance', href: '/best/uk-expat-insurance' },
  { title: 'Best Gulf Region Insurance', href: '/best/gulf-region-insurance' },
  { title: 'Best US Coverage Insurance', href: '/best/us-coverage-insurance' },
];

const comparisonColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'ukNetwork', header: 'UK Network' },
  { key: 'gulfNetwork', header: 'Gulf Network' },
  { key: 'pakistanCoverage', header: 'Pakistan Coverage' },
  { key: 'price', header: 'Starting Price' },
];

const comparisonRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', ukNetwork: 'Strong', gulfNetwork: 'Strong', pakistanCoverage: 'Add-on', price: '$170/mo' },
  { provider: 'Bupa Global', ukNetwork: 'Excellent', gulfNetwork: 'Excellent', pakistanCoverage: 'Add-on', price: '$190/mo' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', ukNetwork: 'Strong', gulfNetwork: 'Strong', pakistanCoverage: 'Add-on', price: '$165/mo' },
  { provider: 'Now Health', ukNetwork: 'Good', gulfNetwork: 'Excellent', pakistanCoverage: 'Included', price: '$155/mo' },
  { provider: 'Jubilee Life', ukNetwork: 'Limited', gulfNetwork: 'Good', pakistanCoverage: 'Included', price: '$100/mo' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Best Health Insurance for Pakistani Expats 2026"
  description="Compare international health insurance for Pakistani expats. Find coverage for the UK, Gulf countries, US, and other destinations."
  headline="Best Insurance for Pakistani Expats in 2026"
  subheadline="Pakistan's diaspora is one of the world's largest—with major communities in the UK, Gulf states, and North America. Here's how to stay protected abroad."
  heroBackgroundImage="/images/pages/pakistani-expat-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Get Cigna Quote →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna"
>
  <h2 id="top-picks">Our Top Picks</h2>
  <p>
    Pakistani expats are concentrated in the UK, UAE, Saudi Arabia, US, and Canada. Healthcare costs vary dramatically—the UK offers NHS access while the US requires comprehensive coverage. Here's what we recommend:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Best overall for Pakistani expats. Strong networks in the UK and Gulf, comprehensive coverage, reliable service.</li>
    <li><strong>Bupa Global:</strong> Premium option with excellent worldwide networks. Outstanding UK coverage.</li>
    <li><strong>Now Health:</strong> Strong Gulf presence with Pakistan coverage often included. Good for UAE/Saudi-based expats.</li>
    <li><strong>Allianz Care:</strong> Good global coverage at competitive prices.</li>
    <li><strong>Jubilee Life:</strong> Pakistani insurer with some international products. Familiar brand, includes Pakistan coverage.</li>
  </ul>

  <CTABox
    title="UK vs Gulf Coverage"
    description="The UK offers NHS access to legal residents—many Pakistani expats supplement with private insurance for faster access. Gulf countries require employer-provided insurance, but quality varies. Understand your destination's system."
    buttonText="Compare Options"
    buttonHref="/go/cigna"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="leaving-pakistan">Leaving Pakistani Healthcare</h2>
  <p>
    Pakistan has a mixed public-private healthcare system. Here's what happens when you leave:
  </p>

  <h3>Public Healthcare</h3>
  <p>
    Pakistan's public healthcare system provides basic services but is under-resourced. There's no formal social health insurance that extends internationally. Moving abroad means arranging independent coverage.
  </p>

  <h3>EOBI (Employees' Old-Age Benefits Institution)</h3>
  <p>
    EOBI provides pension and limited benefits for formal sector workers. It doesn't include international healthcare coverage. Overseas Pakistanis need separate health insurance.
  </p>

  <h3>Private Pakistani Insurance</h3>
  <p>
    Private health insurance from Pakistani companies (Jubilee, EFU, Adamjee) typically provides limited international coverage—usually emergency treatment abroad for short periods. Long-term stays overseas require dedicated international coverage.
  </p>

  <h3>Sehat Sahulat Programme</h3>
  <p>
    The government's health insurance program covers eligible families but only within Pakistan. It provides no international coverage.
  </p>

  <h2 id="destination-considerations">Destination Considerations</h2>
  <p>
    Pakistani expats face different situations depending on destination:
  </p>

  <h3>United Kingdom</h3>
  <p>
    The UK has the largest Pakistani diaspora outside Pakistan. NHS provides free healthcare to legal residents with proper visa status. Many Pakistani expats supplement NHS with private insurance for faster specialist access and private hospital options.
  </p>

  <h3>Gulf Countries (UAE, Saudi, Qatar, Kuwait)</h3>
  <p>
    Large Pakistani workforce in the Gulf. Employer-provided insurance is mandatory but quality varies significantly. Basic employer plans may have limitations—supplemental international insurance provides security and better benefits.
  </p>

  <h3>United States</h3>
  <p>
    Growing Pakistani community, especially in Texas, New York, and California. US healthcare is extremely expensive—comprehensive coverage is essential. Employer plans are common but end with employment.
  </p>

  <h3>Canada</h3>
  <p>
    Provincial healthcare after waiting period (typically 3 months). Toronto and Calgary have significant Pakistani populations. International insurance covers the waiting period.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Currency Considerations</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800">
      The Pakistani rupee has experienced volatility. USD or GBP-denominated policies provide stability—your coverage maintains its value regardless of rupee movements. Consider this when budgeting for premiums.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="comparison-table">Quick Comparison</h2>
  <ComparisonTable columns={comparisonColumns} rows={comparisonRows} />

  <h2 id="detailed-reviews">Detailed Reviews</h2>

  <h3>Cigna Global</h3>
  <p>
    Cigna Global offers comprehensive international coverage ideal for Pakistani expats. Strong networks in the UK (largest diaspora destination) and Gulf countries. Plans come in three tiers with coverage up to unlimited.
  </p>

  <p>
    24/7 English service, direct billing at major hospitals worldwide. Pakistan coverage can be added for visits home.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>Best for:</strong> Pakistani expats who want reliable global coverage, especially in the UK or Gulf.
  </p>

  <h3>Bupa Global</h3>
  <p>
    Bupa Global offers premium international coverage with excellent UK networks—particularly valuable for UK-based Pakistani expats. Service quality is outstanding with comprehensive benefits.
  </p>

  <p>
    Higher pricing reflects premium quality. Best for professionals who can afford top-tier coverage.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>Best for:</strong> Pakistani professionals in the UK who want the best coverage available.
  </p>

  <h3>Now Health</h3>
  <p>
    Now Health has strong presence in Asia and the Gulf—regions with large Pakistani expat populations. Pakistan coverage is often included automatically. Good option for UAE or Saudi-based expats.
  </p>

  <p>
    Service is good, pricing is competitive for Gulf coverage.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>Best for:</strong> Pakistani expats in Gulf countries who want included Pakistan coverage.
  </p>

  <h3>Allianz Care</h3>
  <p>
    Allianz Care offers good global coverage at competitive prices. Strong networks in Europe and adequate coverage elsewhere. Good option for Pakistani expats in European destinations.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>Best for:</strong> Pakistani expats seeking good value with global coverage.
  </p>

  <h3>Jubilee Life</h3>
  <p>
    Jubilee Life is one of Pakistan's largest insurers and offers some international products. Familiar brand, familiar processes, Pakistan coverage included. International networks are more limited than dedicated international insurers.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>Best for:</strong> Pakistani expats who prefer familiar Pakistani service and primarily need Pakistan coverage.
  </p>

  <CTABox
    title="Compare Your Options"
    description="Get quotes from multiple providers to find the best balance of network strength, coverage, and price for your destination."
    buttonText="Get Free Quotes"
    buttonHref="/go/cigna"
  />

  <h2 id="popular-destinations">Popular Destinations</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance needs vary by destination. Here's what Pakistani expats should consider:
  </p>

  <h3>United Kingdom</h3>
  <p>
    Largest Pakistani community outside Pakistan, especially in Birmingham, Bradford, London, and Manchester. NHS provides base coverage for legal residents. Private insurance offers faster access and additional benefits. Many Pakistani-origin doctors practice in the NHS.
  </p>

  <h3>United Arab Emirates</h3>
  <p>
    Dubai and Abu Dhabi have large Pakistani communities. Health insurance is mandatory—employers must provide it. Many Pakistani doctors practice in the UAE. Supplemental coverage ensures better benefits.
  </p>

  <h3>Saudi Arabia</h3>
  <p>
    Large Pakistani workforce. Employer-provided insurance is mandatory but coverage quality varies. International insurance can supplement basic employer plans for better access.
  </p>

  <h3>United States</h3>
  <p>
    Growing community in Texas, New York, California, and Illinois. US healthcare is extremely expensive—comprehensive coverage is essential. Don't rely solely on employer coverage.
  </p>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
    <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border border-neutral-200">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">Does Pakistani insurance cover me abroad?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Most Pakistani policies provide very limited international coverage (emergency only, short periods). For living abroad, you need dedicated international health insurance.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border border-neutral-200">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">Do I need insurance in the UK?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">NHS covers legal residents. Private insurance is optional but provides faster access, private rooms, and choice of specialists. Many Pakistani expats supplement NHS coverage.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border border-neutral-200">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">Is Gulf employer insurance enough?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Quality varies significantly. Some employer plans are comprehensive; others have major limitations. Review your plan carefully and consider supplemental coverage.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border border-neutral-200">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">What about coverage during Pakistan visits?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Most international insurers offer Pakistan as a coverage region. Jubilee and Now Health include it automatically. Confirm details with your chosen provider.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border border-neutral-200">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">Can I cover family in Pakistan?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">International expat policies typically cover spouse and dependent children with you abroad. Family remaining in Pakistan need separate Pakistani health insurance.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border border-neutral-200">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">Are there Pakistani doctors abroad?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Yes, especially in the UK (many in NHS), Gulf countries, and US. Your insurer covers any qualified doctor, and Pakistani community networks can help find familiar providers.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2>Final Verdict</h2>
  <p>
    Pakistani expats need comprehensive international insurance—Pakistani coverage doesn't extend abroad meaningfully. <strong>Cigna Global</strong> is our top recommendation for reliable coverage in the UK and Gulf. <strong>Bupa Global</strong> offers premium UK coverage.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>Now Health</strong> suits Gulf-based expats who want included Pakistan coverage. <strong>Allianz Care</strong> provides good value globally. <strong>Jubilee Life</strong> works for those who prefer familiar Pakistani service.
  </p>

  <p>
    In the UK, NHS provides base coverage—private insurance is supplementary. In the Gulf and US, comprehensive coverage is essential. Don't rely solely on employer coverage.
  </p>

</PageShell>
